Description:
•	Three female civilians physically assaulted a 15-year-old pregnant girl in Hai Twara neighbourhood, Yambio town, Yambio County;
On 22 April, a secondary source (service provider) reported that on 14 April, three female civilians, one of whom was armed with a knife, physically assaulted a 15-year-old pregnant girl (name on file, however, ethnicity unknown) in Hai Twara neighbourhood of Yambio town. According to the source, the attack was orchestrated by her estranged 17-year-old lover, who had impregnated her. Reportedly, the assailants ambushed and attacked the victim, intending to cause her to miscarry. Reportedly, during the assault, the victim lost consciousness and was subsequently evacuated to Yambio Hospital for medical treatment. A source confirmed that the victim remains pregnant, and the incident has been officially reported to Yambio Police Station for investigation. 
Comment: HRD will conduct a follow-up visit to Yambio police station to gather information on the status of the case

